{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"424e16c0-aaf4-486e-a5d2-767692024cfe","content":"Here's the skip attribute for each framework:\n\n**MSTest**\n```csharp\n[TestMethod]\n[Ignore(\"Reason for skipping\")]\npublic void MyTest() { }\n```\n\n**xUnit**\n```csharp\n[Fact(Skip = \"Reason for skipping\")]\npublic void MyTest() { }\n\n// For Theory:\n[Theory(Skip = \"Reason for skipping\")]\npublic void MyTest(int x) { }\n```\n\n**NUnit**\n```csharp\n[Test]\n[Ignore(\"Reason for skipping\")]\npublic void MyTest() { }\n```\n\n**TUnit**\n```csharp\n[Test]\n[Skip(\"Reason for skipping\")]\npublic void MyTest() { }\n```\n\nKey differences: xUnit puts `Skip` on the test attribute itself (not a separate attribute), while the others use a dedicated attribute. MSTest and NUnit both use `[Ignore]`, and TUnit uses `[Skip]`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"3e66067d-eb16-48c1-94db-3a9da8a5f7da","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about how to skip tests with a reason message in each of the four .NET test frameworks. This is a knowledge question about test framework APIs. Let me provide a concise answer from my knowledge.","outputTokens":291,"requestId":"7033:1ED665:B3A036:CF77BF:69F2AC40"},"id":"8aba6665-fca7-4ac5-a887-631d50ef6f07","timestamp":"2026-04-30T01:11:34.840Z","parentId":"7aaa271f-ac68-498d-8927-24e0e1343553"}
